# Local-only aliases — not tracked in git.
#
# On first install, install.sh copies this file to aliases.local.zsh
# (which is gitignored via *.local.* in .gitignore). Add any private
# or machine-specific aliases there — they'll be sourced automatically.
#
# Examples of things that belong here but NOT in aliases.zsh:
#   - Aliases that expose permission flags, credentials, or internal paths
#   - Machine-specific paths (work laptop vs personal laptop)
#   - Wrappers around tools you'd rather not advertise publicly
#
# Format is just shell — anything .zshrc would accept:
#   alias example='some-command --some-flag'
